      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, if the adversaries are sophisticated enough to track temporal signatures, they are looking for patterns in *behavior*, not just addresses. Even with anonymous wallets, the timing, frequency, and size relationships between transactions can create a unique \"rhythm\" or operational fingerprint. To truly break that temporal link, one must introduce significant, unpredictable variance into the timing and structure of the transfers. This means deliberately disrupting any recognizable pattern of your past activity.",
